alert.note: Alert for Kewaunee (Wisconsin) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 01 at 8:55PM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Kewaunee River near Kewaunee affecting Kewaunee County. ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Kewaunee River near Kewaunee. * WHEN...Until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 14.0 feet, Water approaches Ransom Moore Lane near highway FF. Stream flow upstream may become faster due to increasing elevation as well as localized flooding. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 8:30 PM CDT Saturday the stage was 14.6 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 8:30 PM CDT Saturday was 14.8 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 14.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 14.4 feet on 07/06/1993. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Sunday morning (April 2). Sunday afternoon.
